      "content": "\"configuration error\" is okay, but even that sounds like we messed up. if we say it was an error, people are going to ask why it happened in the first place. \n\ncould we pull it off by saying this was just part of a scheduled system optimization or a routine backend update where some metadata was temporarily visible during the transition? i just want to avoid making it look like we have a security problem when we don't.",
